28/09/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The cabinet on Monday (27 September) adopted a national programme for NATO membership for the period 2004-2005.
Afterwards, Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva said passage of the document represented a major phase in the NATO integration process and reaffirmed the government's preparedness to implement related obligations.
Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski said that in addition to military reforms, the Macedonian government was urged to concentrate on fulfilling the set political requirements.
Also Monday, Macedonia's State Election Commission said it is completing preparations for the 7 November referendum on the new decentralisation laws.
Campaigning is to begin on 8 October.
(Vest, Utrinski Vesnik - 28/09/04;
A1 TV - 27/09/04)
